description:
Extend the versioned registry spec to support metadata on version entries.

## Metadata Fields
- `deprecated: bool` - Mark version as deprecated
- `deprecationMessage: string` - Migration guidance
- `eol: string` - End of life date (ISO 8601)

## Example
```nix
versions = {
  "1.22" = {
    package = final.go_1_22;
    deprecated = true;
    deprecationMessage = "Use 1.23 instead";
    eol = "2025-02-01";
  };
};
```

## Behavior
- Warn (not error) when instantiating deprecated toolchains
- Warn when EOL date has passed
- Provide clear migration guidance in warning message
- Consider environment variable to suppress warnings

## Implementation Notes
- Needs backward compatibility: plain derivations should still work
- Detection: check if version entry has `package` attribute
- Wire warnings into Turnkey's toolchain resolution

Related: docs/specs/versioned-registry.md
Depends on: turnkey-xcpo implementation
